Section 1:
1 L.D. 662
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 VETERANS AND LEGAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 430, L.D. 662, “An Act to Fund Military
10 Sexual Trauma Liaisons”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Support Survivors of Military Sexual Trauma and Active Duty Military
13 Members Transitioning to Civilian Life'
14 Amend the bill by inserting after the title and before the enacting clause the following:
15 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
16 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
17 Whereas, veterans have made significant sacrifices to protect our country and ensure
18 our freedom, and many of those veterans in Maine may face challenges transitioning back
19 to civilian life; and
20 Whereas, the Legislature remains committed to supporting efforts that assist military
21 service members and their families as they separate from military service and transition
22 back to civilian life by helping them find stable employment, access health care and
23 housing and find their place in society; and
24 Whereas, it is particularly important to support those veterans who have sacrificed
25 more than others because they have experienced military sexual trauma while serving their
26 country in the military; and
27 Whereas, this legislation needs to take effect before the expiration of the 90-day
28 period to provide desperately needed funding to organizations that support veterans and
29 their families; and
30 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
31 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
32 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
33 therefore,'
Page 1 - 132LR1333(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 430, L.D. 662
1 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
2 following:
3 'Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §13056-K is enacted to read:
4 §13056-K. Active Duty Military Transition to Civilian Life Fund and Program
5 1. Fund established; purpose. The Active Duty Military Transition to Civilian Life
6 Fund, referred to in this section as "the fund," is established within the department as an
7 Other Special Revenue Funds account for the purpose of receiving funds for the program.
8 2. Program established; purpose. The Active Duty Military Transition to Civilian
9 Life Program, referred to in this section as "the program," is established within the
10 department to support organizations in the State conducting outreach and providing support
11 services to active duty military members and their families who are transitioning to civilian
12 life.
13 3. Fund sources; administration. The fund consists of money appropriated or
14 allocated to the fund or received from public or private sources. Through agreements or
15 cooperative arrangements, the department may receive, administer and disburse any funds
16 or contributions from a state or federal agency, person, firm or corporation, either
17 independently or in conjunction with state funds appropriated or allocated to the fund for
18 the purposes of this section.
19 4. Funds held separate; interest credited; nonlapsing. The funds in the fund must
20 be held separate and apart from all other money, funds and accounts. Interest earned by
21 the fund must be credited to the fund. Any unexpended balances remaining in the fund at
22 the end of any fiscal year do not lapse and must be carried forward to the next fiscal year.
23 Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §2430, sub-§3, as amended by PL 2021, c. 181, Pt. A, §2, is
24 repealed.
25 Sec. 3. 22 MRSA §2430, sub-§3-A is enacted to read:
26 3-A. Uses of fund. As allocated by the Legislature, the fund may be used for:
27 A. Expenses of the department to administer this chapter;
28 B. Grants for research regarding cannabis for medical use in accordance with
29 subsection 5;
30 C. Grants to organizations in the State conducting outreach and providing support
31 services to active duty military members and their families who are transitioning to
32 civilian life. Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, on or before
33 September 30, 2025, and by every September 30th thereafter, the State Controller shall
34 transfer $200,000 from the fund to the Active Duty Military Transition to Civilian Life
35 Fund established within the Department of Economic and Community Development
36 under Title 5, section 13056-K to administer grants issued pursuant to this paragraph;
37 and
38 D. Grants to organizations in the State providing housing and support services for
39 unhoused veterans and their children and for survivors of military sexual trauma.
40 Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, on or before September 30, 2025,
41 and by every September 30th thereafter, the State Controller shall transfer $285,000
Page 2 - 132LR1333(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 430, L.D. 662
412 from the fund to the Survivors of Military Sexual Trauma Fund under section 3971 to
423 administer grants issued pursuant to this paragraph.
3 Sec. 4. 22 MRSA c. 1069 is enacted to read:
4 CHAPTER 1069
5 SURVIVORS OF MILITARY SEXUAL TRAUMA FUND AND PROGRAM
6 §3971. Survivors of Military Sexual Trauma Fund and Program
7 1. Fund established; purpose. The Survivors of Military Sexual Trauma Fund,
8 referred to in this section as "the fund," is established within the department. The fund may
9 receive money from any available state, federal or private source. The fund may not lapse
10 but must be carried forward to carry out the purposes of this section.
11 2. Program established; purpose. The Survivors of Military Sexual Trauma
12 Program, referred to in this section as "the program," is established within the department
13 to assist organizations in the State that provide housing and support services for unhoused
14 veterans and their children and for survivors of military sexual trauma.
15 3. Uses of fund. The fund may be used to support the program.
16 Sec. 5. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
17 allocations are made.
18 ECONOMIC AND COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT, DEPARTMENT OF
19 Active Duty Military Transition to Civilian Life Fund N525
20 Initiative: Provides ongoing allocations to support organizations in the State conducting
21 outreach and providing support services to active duty military members and their families
22 who are transitioning to civilian life.
23 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS 2025-26 2026-27
24 All Other $200,000 $200,000
25 __________ __________
