23 Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
24 takes effect when approved.'
25 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
26 number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment:
29 1. Provides an ongoing annual transfer of $200,000 from the Medical Use of Cannabis
30 Fund to the Active Duty Military Transition to Civilian Life Fund established within the
31 Department of Economic and Community Development to support organizations in the
32 State that conduct outreach and provide support services to active duty military members
33 and their families who are transitioning to civilian life;
34 2. Creates the Survivors of Military Sexual Trauma Program within the Department
35 of Health and Human Services to assist organizations in the State that provide housing and
36 support services for unhoused veterans and their children and for survivors of military
37 sexual trauma;
38 3. Provides an ongoing annual transfer of $285,000 from the Medical Use of Cannabis
39 Fund to the Survivors of Military Sexual Trauma Fund established within the Department
40 of Health and Human Services to support organizations in the State that provide housing
41 and support services for unhoused veterans and their children and for survivors of military
42 sexual trauma;
Page 4 - 132LR1333(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 430, L.D. 662
1 4. Modifies the provision of law governing the Medical Use of Cannabis Fund to allow
2 the fund to be used for these purposes; and
3 5. Adds an emergency preamble and emergency clause.
